documentation.text:
@dev Calculates the necessary slippage adjustment for the {vaderDeposited} and {assetDeposited}
 amounts across the total {vaderBalance} and {assetBalance} amounts.

@dev Calculates the loss based on the supplied {releasedVader} and {releasedAsset}
 compared to the supplied {originalVader} and {originalAsset}.

@dev Calculates the {amountOut} of the swap based on the supplied {amountIn}
 across the supplied {reserveIn} and {reserveOut} amounts.

documentation.text:
@dev Calculates the {amountIn} of the swap based on the supplied {amountOut}
 across the supplied {reserveIn} and {reserveOut} amounts.
@dev Calculates the difference between the supplied {a} and {b} values as a positive number.
@dev Calculates the power of 2 of the supplied {a} value.

@dev Calculates the square root {c} of the supplied {a} value utilizing the Babylonian method:
 https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Methods_of_computing_square_roots#Babylonian_method

calculateLiquidityUnits(uint256,uint256,.details: Calculates the amount of liquidity units for the {vaderDeposited} and {assetDeposited} amounts across {totalPoolUnits}. The {vaderBalance} and {assetBalance} are taken into account in order to calculate any necessary slippage adjustment.

calculateLoss(uint256,uint256,uint256,ui.details: Calculates the loss based on the supplied {releasedVader} and {releasedAsset} compared to the supplied {originalVader} and {originalAsset}.

calculateSlipAdjustment(uint256,uint256,.details: Calculates the necessary slippage adjustment for the {vaderDeposited} and {assetDeposited} amounts across the total {vaderBalance} and {assetBalance} amounts.

calculateSwap(uint256,uint256,uint256).details: Calculates the {amountOut} of the swap based on the supplied {amountIn} across the supplied {reserveIn} and {reserveOut} amounts.

calculateSwapReverse(uint256,uint256,uin.details: Calculates the {amountIn} of the swap based on the supplied {amountOut} across the supplied {reserveIn} and {reserveOut} amounts.

delta(uint256,uint256).details: Calculates the difference between the supplied {a} and {b} values as a positive number.

pow(uint256).details: Calculates the power of 2 of the supplied {a} value.

root(uint256).details: Calculates the square root {c} of the supplied {a} value utilizing the Babylonian method: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Methods_of_computing_square_roots#Babylonian_method
